es it is smaller than the local fragmentation length.\nThese smaller spacings observed with the SMA can be explained by either a\nhelical magnetic field, cloud rotation, or/and global filament collapse.\nFinally, possible evidence for sequential fragmentation is suggested in the\nnorthern part of the OMC-3 filament.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 29 Nov 2012 08:39:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
