rantee that the\napproximate solution of $Ax=b$ satisfies a desired accuracy. Given the fact\nthat irregular sparse linear systems are common in applications, this approach\nwidely extends the practicability of SPAI and PSAI. Numerical results\ndemonstrate the considerable superiority of our approach to the direct\napplication of SPAI and PSAI to $Ax=b$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 29 Nov 2012 10:23:45 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 17 Dec 2012 02:22:22 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 1 Apr 2013 01:54:14 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 16 Mar 2015 13:47:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-03-17"}
